In this article, the author calls on the American people to honor the history and achievements of Black Americans during Black History Month. They emphasize the need to reflect on the struggles Black Americans have faced and the ongoing systemic racism in the country. The author mentions the summer of protests following the killing of George Floyd and the disproportionate impact of the pandemic on Black Americans. They also highlight the recent attack on the Capitol by insurrectionists and white supremacists, emphasizing the battle for the soul of America. The author states that the Biden-Harris Administration is committed to addressing these issues and advancing racial justice and equity in various areas, including healthcare, education, housing, the economy, the environment, the justice system, and the electoral process. They argue that doing so is not only the right thing to do but also beneficial for the nation as a whole.